So, what would it mean if corporate boards
faced stricter scrutiny over their speech-related decisions? While the prec=
ise implications remain fluid, it might be time for a reassessment of the o=
ngoing battle against misinformation. Perhaps, for the sake of the First Am=
endment, it=E2=80=99s not in anyone=E2=80=99s best interest if Fox loses?

